Natural history of claudicants with critical hemodynamic indices. We reviewed the records of approximately 1,500 patients seen in the Vascular Laboratory of the Cincinnati Veterans Affairs Medical Center from 1980 to 1987 and identified 23 patients (25 limbs) who met all of the following criteria: 1) an ankle/brachial index less than or equal to 0.35 2) an ankle or transmetatarsal pulse volume recording less than or equal to 3 mm in amplitude